                        <h6 class="heading .centro"> Brick Breaker </h6>
                        <div class="content">         

                            <p>Simple Brick Breaker game, created using C and OpenGL</p>

                            <p>This was the first game we have ever made back in 2012 on freshman year during our first full night long programming sprint. I picked it up a couple of days ago to dust it off. I modulated the code, used pointers instead of global variables where it was possible (some GLUT functions are void only) and fixed some bugs </p>

                            <p>The controls are pretty simple. Use the arrow keys to move the pad. Press the spacebar to start the game. After beating the game or losing it, press "s" to play again or "n" to not</p>

                            <p> For a little more in depth read, check out the <span><a href="/Relatorio final de iniciacao cientifica - Daniel de Araujo Pereira.pdf">report</a></span> written by the end of the research (in portuguese only for now, sorry! Working on the translation)

